  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      We study blood sugars in the children with T1DM, who are given insulin detemir and a rapid
      acting insulin. We hypothesize that there is no difference in the patterns of blood sugars
      when detemir is given in the same syringe or in separate syringes with rapid acting insulin.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
